#!/bin/sh
# Before each commit: (0) regenerate the COMMITTED pre-warm cache (bundles/cache/)
# from the current sources — so the curated precompiled artifacts stay in step
# with the tree; each is self-validating, so a skipped regen only costs the
# compiler-free fast path, never correctness (tools/internal/prewarm.mjs). (0b) bake the
# homepage's static extraction into index.html (tools/internal/bake-homepage-crawler.mjs) so the
# root page carries its content for crawlers + LLMs; host-client clears it at boot,
# so a stale bake would only ever affect the crawler snapshot, never a live user.
# (1) rebuild any STALE platform bundle — stamp-version calls
# tools/internal/bundle-freshness.mjs first, so a commit cannot ship a bundles artifact older
# than its inputs; (2) stamp the cache-busting BUILD_ID so every deploy carries a
# build id that reflects the current platform (runtime + bundles + web client + SW +
# committed cache + baked index.html). Idempotent: nothing relevant moved → no regen,
# no rebake, no rebuild, no restamp, no churn.
#
# Order matters: prewarm + bake write BEFORE stamp-version hashes bundles/ and
# index.html into the BUILD_ID, so a source change rebumps the id (dropping the SW
# cache bucket on deploy).
#
# Committed + shared (not the per-clone .git/hooks/ copy). `npm install` wires it up via the
# package.json "prepare" script; to activate by hand: git config core.hooksPath tools/hooks
node tools/internal/prewarm.mjs || exit 0
node tools/internal/doc/assemble.mjs || exit 0
node tools/internal/bake-homepage-crawler.mjs || exit 0
node tools/internal/stamp-version.mjs || exit 0
git add service-worker.js bundles index.html 2>/dev/null
exit 0
